u_t(x,t)=\alpha^2 u_{xx}(x,t)
(x,t)\in \mathbb R\times [0,\infty)
x
\mathcal F(\alpha^2 u_{xx})=-\alpha^2 \xi^2 \mathcal F(u)
\mathcal F(u_t)=\frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi}}\int_{-\infty}^{\infty}\frac{\partial}{\partial t}u e^{-ix\xi}dx=\frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi}}\frac{d}{dt}\int_{-\infty}^\infty ue^{-ix\xi}dx = \frac{d}{dt}\mathcal F(u)
